The chimera is a type of creature composed of many different type of animals. A classical chimera has the body of a gigantic goat, but the hind parts of a serpent and the front part and head of a lion. Sometimes it has the head of all three of these.

The original chimera is the progeny of the monstrous Achidne and Typhon, and its siblings were [[Cerberus]], the serpentine [[Hydra]], and the enigmatic Sphinx
